p: The effect of cell line on DENV-2 virus titers was determined by following the above protocol in a mammalian cell line (BHK21 c15) and a mosquito cell line with a dysfunctional RNA interference pathway (C6/36) [ 27, 28]. C6/36 cells were seeded at 1.5x10 6 cells/well and BHK cells were seeded at 5x10 5 cells/ well in 12 well plates. The following day, both cell lines were infected with DENV-2 and treated with 1% DMSO, 1 μM torin-1 or 10 μM spautin-1. Titers were harvested at 48 hpi. Each experiment was completed in triplicate with two biological replicates per experimental replicate.
